\begin{definition}
A \emph{Moyal's quantizer} for $(X,\mu,\mathcal{H})$ is a mapping $\Omega$ of $X$ into the space of bounded self adjoint operators on $\mathcal{H}$ such that $\Omega(X)$ is weakly dense in $\mathcal{L}(\mathcal{H})$, and moreover it has to verify
\begin{equation}
	Tr(\Omega(u))=1
\end{equation}
\begin{equation}
	Tr(\Omega(u)\Omega(v))=\delta(u-v)
\end{equation}
